Los Soñadores/Dreamers Video Premiere!

I am so proud and happy to present this great video by my friend and producer Richie Briñez. I want to thank Yumaria Grijt, vocalist and lyricist, and the amazing musicians involved in the project: John Benitez (acoustic bass), Louie Bauzo (percussion), Klaus Mueller (piano), Ludwig Afonso (drums), and Jerome Goldschmidt (percussion).

Special thanks to all the photographers who granted us permission to use their photos in the video. I am also grateful to Marcella Joya for her great pictures from the studio and her help with the text about the video.

#Dreamers #DACA #LosSoñadores #ElViolinLatino

snapshot.link_description:
Los Soñadores/Dreamers

How did Gregor Huebner, a German composer, and violinist of contemporary music, fall in love with Latin Music, and bring El Violín Latino to life? Blame it on Johnny Almendra, a Brooklyn born percussionist and bandleader, who hired him to play with his hip Salsa band, Los Jóvenes del Barrio. This was in 1995, around the time Gregor decided to move to New York City.

For his album EL Violín Latino Vol. 3, Gregor composed a song titled "Los Soñadores/Dreamers”. The song pays homage to the young adults who immigrated to the United States as little children but remain out of status —no human being is illegal. Under the Trump administration there is great risk of deportation. 

Yumaria Grijt, vocalist and lyricist, traveled to New York from Curacao (her native land and where she still resides) for the recording session with El Violín Latino. Yumaria learned to speak Spanish, as a little girl, by watching Venezuelan telenovelas (soap operas) with her grandmother. As a result, she is able to sing fluently in English and Spanish. The same languages that many DREAMers speak.

As I was filming the recording session and heard Yumarya Grijt singing the lyrics she wrote, I felt there was a story we needed to share; and I felt an urgent need to shout our support for the young immigrants. This video represents our shout to all who might not know what DACA is or what a DREAMer means to this country. It is our hope that the message resonates with you.

The other musicians involved in the project are: John Benitez (acoustic bass), Louie Bauzo (percussion), Klaus Mueller (piano), Ludwig Afonso (drums), and Jerome Goldschmidt (percussion).

I am immensely thankful to all the great photographers who permitted use of their work for this cause. And I am elated with my involvement.
snapshot.title: Status Update

markup.__html: Una de las cosas que más defiendo, y que promulgo desde que Cristo llegó a mi vida, es la pureza sexual, no solo porque es un Mandamiento Divino, sino porque las bendiciones que siguen al sacrificio de haberse mantenido en santidad para Dios, mi Señor, son inmensamente grandes y no tienen comparación.

body_translations.bg_BG: едно от нещата, които защитавам най-много, и което обнародван откакто христос влезе в живота ми, е сексуална чистота, не само защото е божествена заповед, а защото благословиите, които следват саможертвата на да в святост за бога, милорд, те са изключително големи и не могат да се сравняват.
body_translations.de_DE: Eines der Dinge, die ich am meisten verteidige und seit Christus in mein Leben kam, ist die sexuelle Reinheit, nicht nur, weil es ein göttliches Gebot ist, sondern weil die Segnungen, die dem Opfer folgen, in Heiligkeit für Gott gehalten zu werden, mein Herr. .
body_translations.en_XX: One of the things I defend most, and which promulgated since Christ came into my life, is sexual purity, not just because it is a divine commandment, but because the blessings that follow the sacrifice of having kept in holiness for God, my Lord , they are immensely large and have no comparison.
body_translations.zh_TW: 我最捍衛的事情之一, 從基督進入我的生命中頒布的, 是性純潔, 不只是因為它是神聖的命令, 而是因為上帝的祝福, 而犧牲了為上帝的神聖, 我的主, 它們是巨大的, 沒有比較.

markup.__html:
¡Dejen sus preguntas y haremos una serie de programas para uestedes!

Este año 2018, #China celebra el 40º aniversario de la Política de Reforma y Apertura. La reforma y apertura de China iniciada en 1978 ha sido uno de los acontecimientos más importantes en el siglo XX, y los éxitos logrados en los últimos 40 años han mostrado la capacidad y el nivel administrativos del Partido Comunista de China (PCCh). Con el motivo de este festejo, en CGTN en Español plantearemos una serie de vídeos especial para responder sus preguntas sobre los avances que ha logrado China en los últimos 40 años. Las preguntas pueden ser detalladas y de cualquier campo, por ejemplo del desarrollo de la economía china, de la construcción de infraestructuras, de la concienciación ecológica, de los megaproyectos de China, del desarrollo de la ciencia y la tecnología, de la actuación de la sociedad china, etc. Es por eso que les invitamos a que dejen sus preguntas sobre cualquier aspecto que quieran saber sobre China en los últimos 40 años. #ReformayApertura
